        <h3 class="section-title">Articles (chronological)</h3>

        <!-- 2016 -->
        <div class="outreach-item">
          <div class="outreach-title">
            <a href="https://eastasiaforum.org/2016/03/09/aiib-to-unlock-south-asias-economic-potential/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              AIIB to unlock South Asia’s economic potential
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="outreach-meta">East Asia Forum — 9 March 2016</div>
          <div class="outreach-summary">
            Argues that the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB) can catalyse regional integration and growth in South Asia by easing infrastructure bottlenecks—provided trust is built and multi-country oversight is maintained.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2017 -->
        <div class="outreach-item">
          <div class="outreach-title">
            <a href="https://eastasiaforum.org/2017/06/17/chinas-belt-and-road-reaches-nepal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              China’s Belt and Road reaches Nepal
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="outreach-meta">East Asia Forum — 17 June 2017</div>
          <div class="outreach-summary">
            Explains Nepal’s enthusiasm for the BRI as a diversification strategy after the 2015 blockade, while noting limited concrete plans, ecological risks in the Himalaya, and the likelihood of repackaged projects and geopolitical pushback.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2018 -->
        <div class="outreach-item">
          <div class="outreach-title">
            <a href="https://www.livemint.com/Opinion/J7LlSME8pqmAxAS8ZFJExO/Nepals-uncertain-transition-to-federalism.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Nepal’s uncertain transition to federalism
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="outreach-meta">Mint (Livemint) — 18 June 2018</div>
          <div class="outreach-summary">
            Reviews Nepal’s move to a three-tier federal system and highlights unresolved issues in power-sharing, fiscal devolution and administrative staffing that risk muddling accountability during the transition.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2019 -->
        <div class="outreach-item">
          <div class="outreach-title">
            <a href="https://www.hindustantimes.com/analysis/india-should-deliver-on-its-projects-in-nepal-not-worry-about-nepal-joining-the-bri/story-cDnyZ8n23QEQDGVPB7O3GO.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              India should deliver on its projects in Nepal, not worry about Nepal joining the BRI
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="outreach-meta">Hindustan Times — 14 May 2019</div>
          <div class="outreach-summary">
            Urges India to prioritise timely delivery of its own commitments—border infrastructure, trade facilitation and investment linkages—rather than treating Nepal’s BRI engagement as a zero-sum contest with China.
          </div>
        </div>

